When however it is cooled below<lb/>
32 so as to become ice its capacity<lb/>
instantly diminishes but the con-<lb/>
-trary effect takes place when<lb/>
it is converted into steam for in<lb/>
this case its capacity is wonderfully<lb/>
increased. -<lb/>
During the conversion of <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">ice</hi>
            <lb/>
into water there is always a<lb/>
very considerable diminution of<lb/>
