temperature of the surrounding bodies<lb/>
And if a pound of heated water at 172°<lb/>
and a pound of ice at 32° <add xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0">be mixed together</add> there is no<lb/>
increase of temperature, &amp; the excess of the<lb/>
Heat of the warm water disappears<lb/>
altogether as Heat of Fluidity or as latent<lb/>
Heat. -<lb/>
